{"title_page": "Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3", "text_new": "{{eastern name order|Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| image = Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|5|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Szegv\u00e1r]], [[Hungary]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of Szeged|Attila J\u00f3zsef University]]\n| occupation = Writer, poet, editor\n| nationality = [[Hungarians|Hungarian]]\n| genre = \n| subject = \n| movement = \n| notableworks = {{plainlist|\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2011)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2014)\n* ''Vera'' (2019)\n}}\n| spouse = Judit \u00c1rvai\n| awards = [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)\n| website = {{URL|http://grecso.hu/}}\n}}\n'''Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3''' (born 18 May 1976) is a Hungarian writer, poet and editor.\n\n==Biography==\nGrecs\u00f3 was born in [[Szegv\u00e1r]] on 18 May 1976. His younger brother, {{ill|Zolt\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3|hu|Grecs\u00f3 Zolt\u00e1n}}, is a dancer and choreographer.<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\">{{cite news |last1=Blah\u00f3 |first1=Gabriella |title=Grecs\u00f3-l\u00e1zban \u00e9gett Szegv\u00e1r |url=https://library.hungaricana.hu/hu/view/Delmagyarorszag_2007_08/?pg=354&layout=s |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[D\u00e9lmagyarorsz\u00e1g]] |volume=97 |issue=195 |page=7 |date=22 August 2007 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> He graduated from the {{ill|J\u00e1nos Bats\u00e1nyi High School|hu|Csongr\u00e1di Bats\u00e1nyi J\u00e1nos Gimn\u00e1zium, Szakk\u00f6z\u00e9piskola \u00e9s Koll\u00e9gium}} in [[Csongr\u00e1d]]. In 2001, he received a diploma in Hungarian language and literature from the [[University of Szeged|Attila J\u00f3zsef University]] in [[Szeged]].<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /><ref name=\"magvetobio\">{{cite web |title=Szerz\u0151k: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://magveto.hu/index.php?action=szerzo&id=49 |publisher=Magvet\u0151 Kiad\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2001 and 2006, Grecs\u00f3 worked as an editor for the ''{{ill|B\u00e1rka|hu|B\u00e1rka (foly\u00f3irat)}}'' literary journal in [[B\u00e9k\u00e9scsaba]]. From 2007 to 2009, he was the lead editor<!--vezet\u0151szerkeszt\u0151--> of the ''[[N\u0151k Lapja]]'' women's magazine. In 2009, he became the lead editor of the prose and essay section of ''[[\u00c9let \u00e9s Irodalom]]''. From 2006 to 2009, he served as vice-president of {{ill|Sz\u00e9p\u00edr\u00f3k T\u00e1rsas\u00e1ga|hu}} (\"Belletrists' Association\").<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\">{{cite web |title=A 2012-es AEGON M\u0171v\u00e9szeti D\u00edj kit\u00fcntetettje: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszt\u00e1n Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9\u00e9rt |url=https://www.aegon.hu/hirek/2012-es-aegon-muveszeti-dij-kituntetettje.html |publisher=AEGON Biztos\u00edt\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, he achieved widespread fame with his short story collection ''Pletykaanyu'' (\"Gossip Mom\").<ref name=\"forraspletyka\">{{cite journal |last1=Szab\u00f3 |first1=Tibor |title=Tiszt\u00edtott pr\u00f3zasz\u00f6vet \u2014 puszt\u00edt\u00f3 referencialit\u00e1s: ''Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Pletykaanyu'' |journal=[[Forr\u00e1s]] |date=May 2007 |volume=39 |issue=5 |page=105 |url=http://www.forrasfolyoirat.hu/0705/szabo.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-056X }}</ref> This was followed by a number of successful novels: ''Isten hozott'' (\"Welcome\", 2005),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benedek |first1=Anna |title=M\u00e1s-vil\u00e1g: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Isten hozott, Magvet\u0151, 2005 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/mas-vilag.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=20 June 2005 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>  ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (\"Dance School\", 2008),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Darvasi |first1=Ferenc |title=Kritika: Isten hozott, T\u00e1nciskola! |journal=[[Tiszat\u00e1j]] |date=July 2008 |volume=62 |issue=7 |page=92 |url=http://epa.oszk.hu/00700/00713/00203/pdf/tiszataj_EPA00713_2008_07_084-092.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-1167}}</ref> ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (\"You Fit Beside Me\", 2011),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bazs\u00e1nyi |first1=S\u00e1ndor |title=Nem csak elk\u00e9pzeli: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz, Magvet\u0151, 2011 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/nem-csak-elkepzeli.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=26 March 2011 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (\"I Follow You\", 2014),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Horv\u00e1th |first1=Csaba |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Megyek ut\u00e1nad |journal=[[Kort\u00e1rs]] |date=November 2011 |volume=58 |issue=11 |url=https://www.kortarsfolyoirat.hu/archivum/2014/11/arch-grecso-krisztian-megyek-utanad.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0023-415X}}</ref> ''Jelmezb\u00e1l'' (\"Costume Ball\", 2016)<ref>{{cite journal |last1=T\u0151t\u0151s |first1=Dorottya |title=Hol volt, hol nem volt, volt egyszer a reg\u00e9ny |journal=[[Helikon (journal)|Helikon]] |date=25 June 2017 |volume=28 |issue=14 |url=https://www.helikon.ro/hol-volt-hol-nem-volt-volt-egyszer-a-regeny/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=1220-6288}}</ref> and ''Vera'' (2019).<ref>{{cite news |author1=horner |title=Szomor\u00fa-izgul\u00e1s \u2013 Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n Vera c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9r\u0151l |url=https://nepszava.hu/3029710_szomoru-izgulas-grecso-krisztian-vera-cimu-regenyerol |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[N\u00e9pszava]] |date=24 March 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nGrecs\u00f3 also worked as a screenwriter for the films ''{{ill|Hasutasok|hu}}'' (2007) and ''{{ill|Megy a g\u0151z\u00f6s|hu}}'' (2007).<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /> He is the author of the play ''Cig\u00e1nyok'' (\"Gypsies\"), adapted from the play of the same name by {{ill|J\u00f3zsi Jen\u0151 Ters\u00e1nszky|hu|Ters\u00e1nszky J\u00f3zsi Jen\u0151}}, which opened at the {{ill|J\u00f3zsef Katona Theatre|hu|Katona J\u00f3zsef Sz\u00ednh\u00e1z (Budapest)}} in Budapest on 15 October 2010 under the direction of [[G\u00e1bor M\u00e1t\u00e9 (actor)|G\u00e1bor M\u00e1t\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Szemere |first1=Katalin |title=Cig\u00e1nyok, A filoz\u00f3fus \u00e9s a Kispolg\u00e1rok |url=http://nol.hu/kultura/ciganyok__a_filozofus_es_a_kispolgarok-1300490 |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[N\u00e9pszabads\u00e1g]] Online |date=28 February 2012 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> He wrote the book of the highly successful musical ''{{ill|A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak (musical)|hu|lt=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak}}'', based on [[Ferenc Moln\u00e1r]]'s novel ''[[The Paul Street Boys]]'', which premiered in the [[Comedy Theatre of Budapest]] on 5 November 2016.<ref name=\"ligetpuf\">{{cite news |title=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak: legyen szabad a Grund! |url=https://liget.ro/studio/a-pal-utcai-fiuk-legyen-szabad-a-grund |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Liget.ro |date=25 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Matalin |first1=D\u00f3ra |title=Mi\u00e9rt nem lehet jegyet kapni a P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fakra? |url=https://index.hu/kultur/2019/05/31/a_pal_utcai_fiuk_vigszinhaz_eloadas_musical_jegyek/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Index (Hungarian website)|Index]] |date=31 May 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Judit \u00c1rvai, a press relations associate of the {{ill|Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3|hu|lt=Magvet\u0151}} publishing house.<ref>{{cite news |last1=M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros |first1=M\u00e1rton |title=Egy vil\u00e1g, ahonnan n\u00e9zni lehet az \u00e9letet |url=https://kulturpart.hu/2017/10/05/egy_vilag_ahonnan_nezni_lehet_az_eletet |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=Kult\u00farpart |date=5 October 2017 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In 2019, they adopted a girl, Hanna.<ref>{{cite news |last1=J\u00e1nossy |first1=Vill\u0151 |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n betegs\u00e9ge miatt egy id\u0151re leker\u00fclt az \u00f6r\u00f6kbefogad\u00e1si v\u00e1r\u00f3list\u00e1r\u00f3l |url=https://24.hu/kultura/2019/10/22/grecso-krisztian-huzos-atv-spirit-orokbefogadas/ |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[24.hu]] |date=22 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In October 2018, Grecs\u00f3 was diagnosed with [[Human papillomavirus infection|HPV]]-associated [[head and neck cancer]]. He recovered in early 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=R\u00e1kbetegs\u00e9g\u00e9r\u0151l vallott Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://hvg.hu/kultura/20190215_Rakbetegsegerol_vallott_Grecso_Krisztian |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Heti Vil\u00e1ggazdas\u00e1g|HVG]] |date=15 February 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Angyalkacsin\u00e1l\u00e1s'' (1999; poetry)\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001; short stories)\n* ''Isten hozott'' (2005; novel)\n* ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (2008; novel)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2011; novel)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2014; novel)\n* ''Jelmezb\u00e1l: Egy csal\u00e1dreg\u00e9ny mozaikjai'' (2016; novel)\n* ''Harminc \u00e9v naps\u00fct\u00e9s'' (2017; short stories)\n* ''Vera'' (2019; novel)\n* ''Magamr\u00f3l t\u00f6bbet'' (2020; poetry)\n\n==Awards and honours==\n* {{ill|Zsigmond M\u00f3ricz Fellowship|hu|M\u00f3ricz Zsigmond-\u00f6szt\u00f6nd\u00edj}} (1999)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* [[S\u00e1ndor Br\u00f3dy Prize]] (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Gy\u00f6rgy Faludy Prize|hu|Faludy Gy\u00f6rgy-d\u00edj}} (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Istv\u00e1n \u00d6rk\u00e9ny Playwright Fellowship|hu|\u00d6rk\u00e9ny Istv\u00e1n dr\u00e1ma\u00edr\u00f3i \u00f6szt\u00f6nd\u00edj}} (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Tibor D\u00e9ry Prize|hu|D\u00e9ry Tibor-d\u00edj}} (2004)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|AEGON Art Prize|hu|AEGON m\u0171v\u00e9szeti d\u00edj}} (2012)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grecso, Krisztian}}\n[[Category:Hungarian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian male writers]]\n[[Category:Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize recipients]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{eastern name order|Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n}}\n{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] -->\n| name = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| image = Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n (cropped).jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1976|5|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Szegv\u00e1r]], [[Hungary]]\n| alma_mater = [[University of Szeged|Attila J\u00f3zsef University]]\n| occupation = Writer, poet, editor\n| nationality = [[Hungarians|Hungarian]]\n| genre = \n| subject = \n| movement = \n| notableworks = {{plainlist|\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2011)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2014)\n* ''Vera'' (2019)\n}}\n| spouse = Judit \u00c1rvai\n| awards = [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)\n| website = {{URL|http://grecso.hu/}}\n}}\n'''Kriszti\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3''' (born 18 May 1976) is a Hungarian writer, poet and editor.\n\n==Biography==\nGrecs\u00f3 was born in [[Szegv\u00e1r]] on 18 May 1976. His younger brother, {{ill|Zolt\u00e1n Grecs\u00f3|hu|Grecs\u00f3 Zolt\u00e1n}}, is a dancer and choreographer.<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\">{{cite news |last1=Blah\u00f3 |first1=Gabriella |title=Grecs\u00f3-l\u00e1zban \u00e9gett Szegv\u00e1r |url=https://library.hungaricana.hu/hu/view/Delmagyarorszag_2007_08/?pg=354&layout=s |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[D\u00e9lmagyarorsz\u00e1g]] |volume=97 |issue=195 |page=7 |date=22 August 2007 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> He graduated from the {{ill|J\u00e1nos Bats\u00e1nyi High School|hu|Csongr\u00e1di Bats\u00e1nyi J\u00e1nos Gimn\u00e1zium, Szakk\u00f6z\u00e9piskola \u00e9s Koll\u00e9gium}} in [[Csongr\u00e1d]]. In 2001, he received a diploma in Hungarian language and literature from the [[University of Szeged|Attila J\u00f3zsef University]] in [[Szeged]].<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /><ref name=\"magvetobio\">{{cite web |title=Szerz\u0151k: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://magveto.hu/index.php?action=szerzo&id=49 |publisher=Magvet\u0151 Kiad\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nBetween 2001 and 2006, Grecs\u00f3 worked as an editor for the ''{{ill|B\u00e1rka|hu|B\u00e1rka (foly\u00f3irat)}}'' literary journal in [[B\u00e9k\u00e9scsaba]]. From 2007 to 2009, he was the lead editor<!--vezet\u0151szerkezt\u0151--> of the ''[[N\u0151k Lapja]]'' women's magazine. In 2009, he became the lead editor of the prose and essay section of ''[[\u00c9let \u00e9s Irodalom]]''. From 2006 to 2009, he served as vice-president of {{ill|Sz\u00e9p\u00edr\u00f3k T\u00e1rsas\u00e1ga|hu}} (\"Belletrists' Association\").<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\">{{cite web |title=A 2012-es AEGON M\u0171v\u00e9szeti D\u00edj kit\u00fcntetettje: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszt\u00e1n Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9\u00e9rt |url=https://www.aegon.hu/hirek/2012-es-aegon-muveszeti-dij-kituntetettje.html |publisher=AEGON Biztos\u00edt\u00f3 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nIn 2001, he achieved widespread fame with his short story collection ''Pletykaanyu'' (\"Gossip Mom\").<ref name=\"forraspletyka\">{{cite journal |last1=Szab\u00f3 |first1=Tibor |title=Tiszt\u00edtott pr\u00f3zasz\u00f6vet \u2014 puszt\u00edt\u00f3 referencialit\u00e1s: ''Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Pletykaanyu'' |journal=[[Forr\u00e1s]] |date=May 2007 |volume=39 |issue=5 |page=105 |url=http://www.forrasfolyoirat.hu/0705/szabo.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-056X }}</ref> This was followed by a number of successful novels: ''Isten hozott'' (\"Welcome\", 2005),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benedek |first1=Anna |title=M\u00e1s-vil\u00e1g: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Isten hozott, Magvet\u0151, 2005 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/mas-vilag.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=20 June 2005 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>  ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (\"Dance School\", 2008),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Darvasi |first1=Ferenc |title=Kritika: Isten hozott, T\u00e1nciskola! |journal=[[Tiszat\u00e1j]] |date=July 2008 |volume=62 |issue=7 |page=92 |url=http://epa.oszk.hu/00700/00713/00203/pdf/tiszataj_EPA00713_2008_07_084-092.pdf |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0133-1167}}</ref> ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (\"You Fit Beside Me\", 2011),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bazs\u00e1nyi |first1=S\u00e1ndor |title=Nem csak elk\u00e9pzeli: Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz, Magvet\u0151, 2011 |url=https://litera.hu/magazin/kritika/nem-csak-elkepzeli.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Litera |date=26 March 2011 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (\"I Follow You\", 2014),<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Horv\u00e1th |first1=Csaba |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n: Megyek ut\u00e1nad |journal=[[Kort\u00e1rs]] |date=November 2011 |volume=58 |issue=11 |url=https://www.kortarsfolyoirat.hu/archivum/2014/11/arch-grecso-krisztian-megyek-utanad.html |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=0023-415X}}</ref> ''Jelmezb\u00e1l'' (\"Costume Ball\", 2016)<ref>{{cite journal |last1=T\u0151t\u0151s |first1=Dorottya |title=Hol volt, hol nem volt, volt egyszer a reg\u00e9ny |journal=[[Helikon (journal)|Helikon]] |date=25 June 2017 |volume=28 |issue=14 |url=https://www.helikon.ro/hol-volt-hol-nem-volt-volt-egyszer-a-regeny/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |language=Hungarian |issn=1220-6288}}</ref> and ''Vera'' (2019).<ref>{{cite news |author1=horner |title=Szomor\u00fa-izgul\u00e1s \u2013 Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n Vera c\u00edm\u0171 reg\u00e9ny\u00e9r\u0151l |url=https://nepszava.hu/3029710_szomoru-izgulas-grecso-krisztian-vera-cimu-regenyerol |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[N\u00e9pszava]] |date=24 March 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\nGrecs\u00f3 also worked as a screenwriter for the films ''{{ill|Hasutasok|hu}}'' (2007) and ''{{ill|Megy a g\u0151z\u00f6s|hu}}'' (2007).<ref name=\"delmagyarblaho\" /> He is the author of the play ''Cig\u00e1nyok'' (\"Gypsies\"), adapted from the play of the same name by {{ill|J\u00f3zsi Jen\u0151 Ters\u00e1nszky|hu|Ters\u00e1nszky J\u00f3zsi Jen\u0151}}, which opened at the {{ill|J\u00f3zsef Katona Theatre|hu|Katona J\u00f3zsef Sz\u00ednh\u00e1z (Budapest)}} in Budapest on 15 October 2010 under the direction of [[G\u00e1bor M\u00e1t\u00e9 (actor)|G\u00e1bor M\u00e1t\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Szemere |first1=Katalin |title=Cig\u00e1nyok, A filoz\u00f3fus \u00e9s a Kispolg\u00e1rok |url=http://nol.hu/kultura/ciganyok__a_filozofus_es_a_kispolgarok-1300490 |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[N\u00e9pszabads\u00e1g]] Online |date=28 February 2012 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> He wrote the book of the highly successful musical ''{{ill|A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak (musical)|hu|lt=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak}}'', based on [[Ferenc Moln\u00e1r]]'s novel ''[[The Paul Street Boys]]'', which premiered in the [[Comedy Theatre of Budapest]] on 5 November 2016.<ref name=\"ligetpuf\">{{cite news |title=A P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fak: legyen szabad a Grund! |url=https://liget.ro/studio/a-pal-utcai-fiuk-legyen-szabad-a-grund |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=Liget.ro |date=25 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Matalin |first1=D\u00f3ra |title=Mi\u00e9rt nem lehet jegyet kapni a P\u00e1l utcai fi\u00fakra? |url=https://index.hu/kultur/2019/05/31/a_pal_utcai_fiuk_vigszinhaz_eloadas_musical_jegyek/ |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Index (Hungarian website)|Index]] |date=31 May 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Judit \u00c1rvai, a press relations associate of the {{ill|Magvet\u0151 K\u00f6nyvkiad\u00f3|hu|lt=Magvet\u0151}} publishing house.<ref>{{cite news |last1=M\u00e9sz\u00e1ros |first1=M\u00e1rton |title=Egy vil\u00e1g, ahonnan n\u00e9zni lehet az \u00e9letet |url=https://kulturpart.hu/2017/10/05/egy_vilag_ahonnan_nezni_lehet_az_eletet |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=Kult\u00farpart |date=5 October 2017 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In 2019, they adopted a girl, Hanna.<ref>{{cite news |last1=J\u00e1nossy |first1=Vill\u0151 |title=Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n betegs\u00e9ge miatt egy id\u0151re leker\u00fclt az \u00f6r\u00f6kbefogad\u00e1si v\u00e1r\u00f3list\u00e1r\u00f3l |url=https://24.hu/kultura/2019/10/22/grecso-krisztian-huzos-atv-spirit-orokbefogadas/ |accessdate=20 April 2020 |work=[[24.hu]] |date=22 October 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref> In October 2018, Grecs\u00f3 was diagnosed with [[Human papillomavirus infection|HPV]]-associated [[head and neck cancer]]. He recovered in early 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=R\u00e1kbetegs\u00e9g\u00e9r\u0151l vallott Grecs\u00f3 Kriszti\u00e1n |url=https://hvg.hu/kultura/20190215_Rakbetegsegerol_vallott_Grecso_Krisztian |accessdate=19 April 2020 |work=[[Heti Vil\u00e1ggazdas\u00e1g|HVG]] |date=15 February 2019 |language=Hungarian}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* ''Angyalkacsin\u00e1l\u00e1s'' (1999; poetry)\n* ''Pletykaanyu'' (2001; short stories)\n* ''Isten hozott'' (2005; novel)\n* ''T\u00e1nciskola'' (2008; novel)\n* ''Mellettem elf\u00e9rsz'' (2011; novel)\n* ''Megyek ut\u00e1nad'' (2014; novel)\n* ''Jelmezb\u00e1l: Egy csal\u00e1dreg\u00e9ny mozaikjai'' (2016; novel)\n* ''Harminc \u00e9v naps\u00fct\u00e9s'' (2017; short stories)\n* ''Vera'' (2019; novel)\n* ''Magamr\u00f3l t\u00f6bbet'' (2020; poetry)\n\n==Awards and honours==\n* {{ill|Zsigmond M\u00f3ricz Fellowship|hu|M\u00f3ricz Zsigmond-\u00f6szt\u00f6nd\u00edj}} (1999)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* [[S\u00e1ndor Br\u00f3dy Prize]] (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Gy\u00f6rgy Faludy Prize|hu|Faludy Gy\u00f6rgy-d\u00edj}} (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Istv\u00e1n \u00d6rk\u00e9ny Playwright Fellowship|hu|\u00d6rk\u00e9ny Istv\u00e1n dr\u00e1ma\u00edr\u00f3i \u00f6szt\u00f6nd\u00edj}} (2002)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|Tibor D\u00e9ry Prize|hu|D\u00e9ry Tibor-d\u00edj}} (2004)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* [[Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize]] (2006)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" />\n* {{ill|AEGON Art Prize|hu|AEGON m\u0171v\u00e9szeti d\u00edj}} (2012)<ref name=\"magvetobio\" /><ref name=\"aegonbio\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Grecso, Krisztian}}\n[[Category:Hungarian male novelists]]\n[[Category:Hungarian male poets]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Hungarian male writers]]\n[[Category:Attila J\u00f3zsef Prize recipients]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Einstein2", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBiography", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kriszti%C3%A1n_Grecs%C3%B3"}
{"title_page": "Glazunovskaya, Vologda Oblast", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Glazunovskaya\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0413\u043b\u0430\u0437\u0443\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vozhegodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|60|24|N|41|13|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vozhegodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Glazunovskaya''' ({{lang-ru|\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0437\u0443\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Mishutinskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vozhegodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 5 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vozhega]] is 73 km, to Mishutinskaya is 7 km. Yesinskaya, Alferyevskaya, Loshchinskaya, Timoninskaya are the nearest rural localities.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District]]\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Glazunovskaya\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0413\u043b\u0430\u0437\u0443\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vozhegodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|60|24|N|41|13|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vozhegodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Glazunovskaya''' ({{lang-ru|\u0413\u043b\u0430\u0437\u0443\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Mishutinskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vozhegodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 5 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vozhega]] is 73 km, to Mishutinskaya is 7 km. Yesinskaya, Alferyevskaya, Loshchinskaya, Timoninskaya are the nearest rural localities.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vozhegodsky District]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glazunovskaya,_Vologda_Oblast"}
{"title_page": "Bhojpuri cinema", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2019}}\n{{Indian cinema}}\n'''Bhojpuri cinema''', '''Bhojiwood''' or '''Bhollywood''' refers to the [[Indian cinema|Indian]] [[Bhojpuri language]] film industry based in [[Bihar]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailypioneer.com/sunday-edition/agenda/cover-story/bhojiwood-losing-its-lustre.html|title=Bhojiwood Losing Its Lustre|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117122416/http://www.dailypioneer.com/sunday-edition/agenda/cover-story/bhojiwood-losing-its-lustre.html|archivedate=2017-11-17}}</ref>\n\nThe first Bhojpuri talkie film, ''[[Ganga Maiyya Tohe Piyari Chadhaibo]]'', was released in 1963 by Vishwanath Shahabadi. The 80s saw the release of many notable as well as run-of-the-mill Bhojpuri films like ''Bitia Bhail Sayan'', ''Chandwa ke take Chakor'', ''Hamar Bhauji'', ''Ganga Kinare Mora Gaon'' and ''Sampoorna Tirth Yatra''. Bhojpuri cinema has grown in recent years. The Bhojpuri film industry is now a {{INR}}2000 crore industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/bhojpuri-film-industry-now-a-rs-2000-crore-industry/articleshow/57924026.cms|title=Bhojpuri film industry now a Rs 2000 crore industry|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171117180007/https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/media/entertainment/bhojpuri-film-industry-now-a-rs-2000-crore-industry/articleshow/57924026.cms|archivedate=2017-11-17}}</ref> Bhojpuri movies are seen across various parts of [[North America]], Europe, and Asia where second and third generation migrants still speak the language, as well as in [[Guyana]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]], [[Suriname]], [[Fiji]], [[Mauritius]], and [[South Africa]], which has a large Bhojpuri population.<ref name=global>{{cite news|title=Regional pride|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/beyond-business/regional-pride-110062400034_1.html|accessdate=22 February 2014|newspaper=Business standard|date=24 June 2010|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227143917/http://www.business-standard.com/article/beyond-business/regional-pride-110062400034_1.html|archivedate=27 February 2014}}</ref>\n\nhii hero Bhojpuri bhabhi jii\n\n==History==\nIn the 1960s, the first president of India, [[Rajendra Prasad]], who hailed from Bihar, met [[Bollywood]] [[actor]] [[Nazir Hussain]] and asked him to make a movie in Bhojpuri, which eventually led to the release of the first Bhojpuri film in 1963.<ref name=ndtv>{{cite news |title=First Bhojpuri Film To Be Screened During Bihar Divas |url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_Story.aspx?id=ENTEN20110171729&keyword=&subcatg= |archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20170630114737/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_Story.aspx?id=ENTEN20110171729&keyword=&subcatg= |url-status=dead |archive-date=30 June 2017 |publisher=[[NDTV]] Movies |date=17 March 2011 }}</ref> Bhojpuri cinema's history begins with the well-received film ''[[Ganga Maiyya Tohe Piyari Chadhaibo]]'' (\"Mother Ganges, I will offer you a yellow sari\"), which was produced by Biswanath Prasad Shahabadi under the banner of Nirmal Pictures and directed by Kundan Kumar.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0233774/ IMDB] {{webarchive|url=https://www.webcitation.org/6AC5gLhTx?url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0233774/ |date=2012-08-26 }}</ref> Throughout the following decades, films were produced in fits and starts. ''Bidesiya'' (\"Foreigner\", 1963, directed by S. N. Tripathi) and ''Ganga'' (\"Ganges\", 1965, directed by Kundan Kumar) were profitable and popular, but in general Bhojpuri films were not commonly produced in the 1960s and 1970s.\n\nIn the 1980s, enough Bhojpuri films were produced to tentatively make up an industry. Films such as ''Mai'' (\"Mom\", 1989, directed by Rajkumar Sharma) and ''Hamar Bhauji'' (\"My Brother's Wife\", 1983, directed by Kalpataru) continued to have at least sporadic success at the box office. ''[[Nadiya Ke Paar (1982 film)|Nadiya Ke Paar]]'' is a 1982 Hindi-Bhojpuri blockbuster directed by Govind Moonis and starring [[Sachin (actor)|Sachin]], [[Sadhana Singh]], Inder Thakur, Mitali, Savita Bajaj, [[Sheela David]], Leela Mishra and Soni Rathod. However, this trend faded out by the end of the decade. By 1990, the nascent industry seemed to be completely finished.<ref>Tripathy, Ratnakar (2007) 'Bhojpuri Cinema', ''South Asian Popular Culture'', 5:2, 145-165</ref>\n\nThe industry took off again in 2001 with the [[Silver Jubilee]] hit ''Saiyyan Hamar'' (\"My Sweetheart\", directed by Mohan Prasad), which shot its hero, Ravi Kissan, to superstardom.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/29ravi.htm |title= Meet the star of Bhojpuri cinema |author= Subhash K. Jha |date= 29 March 2006 |publisher= Rediff |accessdate= 10 December 2009 |url-status= live |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090621080409/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/mar/29ravi.htm |archivedate= 21 June 2009 }}</ref> This was quickly followed by several other remarkably successful films, including ''Panditji Batai Na Biyah Kab Hoi'' (\"Priest, tell me when I will marry\", 2005, directed by Mohan Prasad) and ''Sasura Bada Paisa Wala'' (\"My father-in-law, the rich guy\", 2005). In a measure of the Bhojpuri film industry's rise, both of these did much better business in the states of [[Bihar]] and [[Uttar Pradesh]] than mainstream Bollywood hits at the time. Both films, made on extremely tight budgets, earned back more than ten times their production costs.<ref>\"Move over Bollywood, Here's Bhojpuri,\" BBC News Online: http://news.bbc.co.uk/go/pr/fr/-/1/hi/world/south_asia/4512812.stm</ref> ''Sasura Bada Paisa Wala'' introduced Manoj Tiwari, formerly a well-loved folk singer, to the wider audiences of Bhojpuri cinema. In 2008, he and Ravi Kissan were the leading actors of Bhojpuri films, and their fees increase with their fame. The extremely rapid success of their films has led to dramatic increases in Bhojpuri cinema's visibility, and the industry now supports an awards show<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.screenindia.com/old/fullstory.php?content_id=14294 |title= Bhojpuri industry On a High |author= Ashish Mitra |date= 8 December 2006 |work= Screen|accessdate=10 December 2009}}</ref> and a trade magazine, ''Bhojpuri City'',<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200804141963.htm |title= Not moving closer to Congress: Shatrughan Sinha |date= 14 April 2008 |work= The Hindu |accessdate= 10 December 2009 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121106030352/http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/009200804141963.htm |archivedate= 6 November 2012 }}</ref> which chronicles the production and release of what are now over 100 films per year.\n\nMany of the major stars of mainstream Bollywood cinema, including [[Amitabh Bachchan]], have recently worked in Bhojpuri films. [[Mithun Chakraborty]]'s Bhojpuri debut ''[[Bhole Shankar (film)|Bhole Shankar]]'', released in 2008, is considered the biggest Bhojpuri hit of all time.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.screenindia.com/news/mithuns-first-bhojpuri-film-creates-record-in-bihar/367841/ |title= Mithun's first Bhojpuri film creates record in Bihar |date= 3 October 2008 |work= Screen |accessdate= 10 December 2009 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20081005022100/http://www.screenindia.com/news/mithuns-first-bhojpuri-film-creates-record-in-bihar/367841/ |archivedate= 5 October 2008 }}</ref> Also in 2008, a 21-minute diploma Bhojpuri film by [[Siddharth Sinha]], ''[[Udedh Bun]]'' (Unravel) was selected for world premiere at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Bhojpuri-cinema-heads-to-Berlin-/articleshow/2764728.cms|title=Bhojpuri cinema heads to Berlin|date=7 February 2008|work=The Times of India|first1=Saurabh|last1=Kapoor|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511075843/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Bhojpuri-cinema-heads-to-Berlin-/articleshow/2764728.cms|archivedate=2018-05-11}}</ref> Later it won the [[National Film Award (India)|National Film Award]] for [[National Film Award for Best Short Fiction Film|Best Short fiction Film]].<ref>[http://india.cineuropa.org/2009/01/discovery-of-2008-siddharth-sinha.html Discovery of 2008: Siddharth Sinha, Silver Bear Winner at Berlin] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100705130313/http://india.cineuropa.org/2009/01/discovery-of-2008-siddharth-sinha.html |date=2010-07-05 }} January 2009.</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cut to fame |url=http://www.expressindia.com/latest-news/cut-to-fame/514294/ |newspaper=[[Indian Express]] |date=8 Sep 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003152743/http://www.expressindia.com/latest-news/cut-to-fame/514294/ |archivedate=2012-10-03 }}</ref>\n\nBhojpuri poet [[Manoj Bhawuk]] has written a history of Bhojpuri cinema.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bhojpuricinema.wordpress.com/bhojpuri-cinema-ke-itihas/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2017-04-16 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130806055852/http://bhojpuricinema.wordpress.com/bhojpuri-cinema-ke-itihas/ |archivedate=2013-08-06 }}</ref> Bhawuk is widely known as \"Encyclopedia of Bhojpuri Cinema\".\n\nIn February 2011, a three-day film and cultural festival in [[Patna]] marking 50 years of Bhojpuri cinema, opened ''Ganga Maiyya Tohe Piyari Chadhaibo'' the first Bhojpuri film. The first Bhojpuri Reality Film \"Dhokha\" is under production under banner Om Kaushik Films is about to be nominated and screened in different International Film Festivals under direction Of Rashmi Raj Kaushik Vicky and Renu Chaudhary.<ref>{{cite news |title=Strong at 50, Bhojpuri cinema celebrates |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/strong-at-50-bhojpuri-cinema-celebrates/749762/0 |newspaper=[[Indian Express]] |date=14 February 2011 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019010957/http://www.indianexpress.com/news/strong-at-50-bhojpuri-cinema-celebrates/749762/0 |archivedate=2012-10-19 }}</ref>\n\n== Notable people ==\nNotable personalities of the Bhojpuri film industry include:\n\n=== Film producers ===\n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Only add a person to this list if they already have their own article on the English Wikipedia \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Please keep the list in alphabetical order by LAST NAME \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n*[[Neetu Chandra]]\n*[[Rajkumar R. Pandey]]\n\n=== Film directors===\n<!-- ONLY ADD A PERSON TO THIS LIST IF THEY ALREADY HAVE AN ENGLISH WIKIPEDIA ARTICLE-->\n*[[Rajnish Mishra]]\n*[[Santosh Mishra]]\n*[[Rajkumar R. Pandey]]\n*[[Ajay Srivastava]]\n*[[S. N. Tripathi]]\n\n=== Actors ===\n{{Main|List of Bhojpuri cinema actors}}\n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Only add a person to this list if they already have their own article on the English Wikipedia \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Please keep the list in alphabetical order by LAST NAME \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Krushna Abhishek]]\n* [[Vinay Anand]]\n* [[Biraj Bhatta]]\n* [[Manoj Bhawuk]]\n* [[KK Goswami]]\n* [[Kamaal Rashid Khan|Kamaal R Khan]]\n* [[Sikandar Kharbanda]]\n* [[Ravi Kishan]]\n* [[Kuldeep Kumar]]\n* [[Sujit Kumar]]\n* [[Awdhesh Mishra]]\n* [[Sanjay Pandey]]\n* [[Pradeep Pandey]]\n* [[Rakesh Pandey]]\n* [[Pawan Singh]]\n* [[Dilip Sinha (actor)|Dilip Sinha]]\n* [[Manoj Tiwari]]\n* [[Dinesh Lal Yadav]]\n* [[Khesari Lal Yadav]]\n{{Div col end}}\n\nApart from these regular actors, many Bollywood actors like [[Amitabh Bachchan]], [[Abhishek Bachchan]], [[Ajay Devgn]], [[Rahul Roy]], [[Dharmendra]], [[Kader Khan]], [[Mithun Chakraborty]], [[Jackie Shroff]], and [[Raj Babbar]],  [[Rahul Dev]], have acted in Bhojpuri movies.<ref name=\"forum.ibodatabase.com\">{{cite web|title=Bollywood actors in Bhojpuri films. Have a look.|url=http://forum.ibodatabase.com/58736/bollywood-actors-in-bhojpuri-films-have-a-look|accessdate=11 January 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111133518/http://forum.ibodatabase.com/58736/bollywood-actors-in-bhojpuri-films-have-a-look|archivedate=11 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Abhishek to star in Bhojpuri film|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1435250/Abhishek-to-star-in-Bhojpuri-film|accessdate=11 January 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140111134415/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/1435250/Abhishek-to-star-in-Bhojpuri-film|archivedate=11 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== Actresses ===\n{{Main|List of Bhojpuri cinema actresses}}\n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Only add a person to this list if they already have their own article on the English Wikipedia \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Please keep the list in alphabetical order by LAST NAME \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Antara Biswas]]\n* [[Rani Chatterjee]]\n* [[Rashami Desai]]\n* [[Amrapali Dubey]]\n* [[Poonam Dubey]]\n* [[Rinku Ghosh]]\n* [[Pakkhi Hegde]]\n* [[Nidhi Jha]]\n* [[Padma Khanna]]\n* [[Nagma]]\n* [[Kajal Raghwani]]\n* [[Rambha (actress)|Rambha]]\n* [[Poonam Sagar]]\n* [[Swati Sen]]\n* [[Sambhavna Seth]]\n* [[Priya Sharma]]\n* [[Shubhi Sharma]]\n* [[Anjana Singh]]\n* [[Seema Singh]]\n* [[Ramya Sri]]\n* [[Jayshree T.]] \n* [[Shweta Tiwari]]\n* [[Swati Verma]]\n\n{{Div col end}}\nApart from these regular actresses, many Bollywood actresses like [[Aruna Irani]], [[Hema Malini]], [[Jaya Bachchan]], [[Juhi Chawla]], [[Rati Agnihotri]] and [[Shilpa Shetty]] are also featured in Bhojpuri movies.<ref name=\"forum.ibodatabase.com\"/>\n\n===Singers===\n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Only add a person to this list if they already have their own article on the English Wikipedia \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n<!---\u2666\u2666\u2666 Please keep the list in alphabetical order by LAST NAME \u2666\u2666\u2666---> \n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n\n* [[Alok Kumar (singer)|Alok Kumar]]\n* [[Sushma Shrestha|Poornima]]\n* [[Kalpana Patowary]]\n* [[Pawan Singh]]\n* [[Indu Sonali]]\n* [[Damodar Raao]]\n* [[Manoj Tiwari]]\n* [[Dinesh Lal Yadav]]\n* [[Khesari Lal Yadav]]\n\n {{Div col end}}\n\nApart from these regular Bhojpuri singers, famous Bollywood singers such as [[Lata Mangeshkar]], [[Asha Bhosle]], [[Usha Mangeshkar]], [[Geeta Dutt]], [[Anuradha Paudwal]], [[Alka Yagnik]], [[Kavita Krishnamurthy]], [[Sonu Nigam]] and [[Udit Narayan]] are featured.\n\n==Notable films==\n{{main|List of Bhojpuri films}}\n<!--FILM(S) WITHOUT AN EXISTING WIKIPEDIA ARTICLE SHOULD NOT BE LISTED HERE!-->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Cast\n|-\n| 1962\n| ''[[Ganga Maiyya Tohe Piyari Chadhaibo]]''\n|[[Nazir Hussain]], [[Kumkum (actress)|Kumkum]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1963\n| ''[[Laagi Nahi Chhute Ram]]''\n|[[Nazir Hussain]], [[Kumkum (actress)|Kumkum]]\n|-\n| ''[[Bidesiya]]''\n|[[Sujit Kumar]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1965\n| ''[[Ganga flim(1965)|Ganga]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Bhouji]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1966\n| ''[[Loha Singh]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1971\n| ''[[Dher Chalaki Jinkara]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1976\n| ''[[Daku Rani Ganga]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1978\n| ''[[Amar Suhagin]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[Balam Pardesia]]''\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|1981\n| ''[[Chanwa Ke Take Chakor]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Saiyan Magan Pahelwani Mein]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Saiyan Tore Karan]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1982\n| ''[[Nadiya Ke Paar (1982 film)|Nadiya Ke Paar]]''\n|[[Sachin (actor)|Sachin]], [[Sadhana Singh]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|1983\n| ''[[Hamar Bhauji]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Chukti Bhar Senur]]''\n|\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[Roos Gailen Saiyen Hamaar]]''\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[Pratigya (2008 film)|Pratigya]]''\n| [[Dinesh Lal Yadav]], [[Pawan Singh]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Devra Bada Satawela]]''\n| [[Pawan Singh]], [[Ravi Kishan]], [[Pradeep Pandey]] (\"Chintu\")\n|-\n|2011\n|[[Deswa]]\n|Ajay Kumar, [[Aarti Puri]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Rakhwala (2013 fil