{"title_page": "Isaac Sesi", "text_new": "[[File:Isaac Sesi.jpg|thumb|Isaac Sesi at the  Africa Prize for Engineering Innovation by the Royal Academy of Engineering.]]\n{{short description|Ghanaian entrepreneur}}'''Isaac Sesi''' is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] [[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]], engineer, and the founder of Sesi Technologies, a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] company that solves agricultural and food challenges.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://citinewsroom.com/2019/06/isaac-sesi-named-mit-technology-review-2019-innovator-under-35/|title=Isaac Sesi named MIT Technology Review 2019 Innovator under 35|date=2019-06-26|website=Citinewsroom - Comprehensive News in Ghana, Current Affairs,  Business News , Headlines, Ghana Sports, Entertainment, Politics,|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanacic.org/clients/15577/|title=Sesi Technologies {{!}} GCIC|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> He is known for his development of a moisture meter to help sub-Saharan African farmers reduce [[Post-harvest losses (grains)|post-harvest losses]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.technologyreview.com/lists/innovators-under-35/2019/inventor/isaac-sesi/|title=Isaac Sesi|website=MIT Technology Review|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.feedthefuture.gov/article/small-gadget-big-impact-young-entrepreneur-fights-food-loss-with-innovation/|title=Small Gadget, Big Impact: Young Entrepreneur Fights Food Loss with Innovation|date=2019-08-30|website=Feed the Future|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nSesi is a graduate of the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology|Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST)]] where he studied [[electrical engineering]]. He completed his senior high school education at [[Mfantsipim School]], where he studied general science.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Career and life ==\n\nSesi is known for developing a moisture metre known as GrainMate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vc4a.com/ventures/sesi-technologies-limited/|title=Sesi Technologies Limited|website=VC4A|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> This device allows farmers and grain traders to measure moisture levels of [[maize]], [[wheat]], [[millet]], and other staple.<ref name=\":0\" /> He is also known to have developed FarmSense, a soil sensing solution for smallholder farmers<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businessworldghana.com/25-year-old-isaac-sesi-ghanas-emerging-agritech-power-house/|title=25-Year-Old Isaac Sesi Is Ghana\u2019s Emerging Agritech Power House|last=webmanager|date=2018-05-26|website=Business World Ghana|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> which made it to the [[Global Innovation through Science and Technology initiative|Global Innovation through Science and Technology]] (GIST) Tech-I Global Pitch competition semifinals.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.feedthefuture.gov/article/small-gadget-big-impact-young-entrepreneur-fights-food-loss-with-innovation/|title=Small Gadget, Big Impact: Young Entrepreneur Fights Food Loss with Innovation|date=2019-08-30|website=Feed the Future|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> His first company was Invent Electronic Company Limited, started in 2014, Which retails electronic components online.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn 2015, he cofounded Wires & Bytes with other three friends to develop web apps and software-as-a-service applications. In 2016 they developed Pasco, an educational app\u00a0 for university students <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsghana.com.gh/ghana-to-become-the-largest-app-developers-soon/|title=Ghana To Become The Largest App Developers Soon|last=Ghana|first=News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> \n\nThe following year he co-founded 2eweboys, a creative writing agency.In 2017, Isaac, then a research engineer at the Department of Agricultural and Biosystems Engineering of the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology]] and Dr Paul Armstrong, a researcher at the United States Department of Agriculture, worked together on a Feed the Future Innovation Lab for the Reduction of Post Harvest Losses Project in partnership with Kansas State University to develop a low-cost moisture meter. The moisture meter was launched at a ceremony in KNUST<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agrilinks.org/post/month-agrilinks-innovations-move-agriculture-forward|title=This Month on Agrilinks: Innovations That Move Agriculture Forward|date=2020-02-03|website=www.agrilinks.org|language=en|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> <ref name=\":4\" />\n\nSince 2018, he has collaborated with different organisations including World Food Programme Ghana, and the\u00a0 Assisting the Management of Poultry and Layer Industries with Feed Improvements and Efficiency Strategies (AMPLIFIES) Ghana Project which is a food for progress program of the [[United States Department of Agriculture|U.S Department of Agriculture]] (USDA) to run post-harvest loss trainings for farmers across Ghana.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wishh.org/amplifies-ghana-partner-isaac-sesi-wins-mit-innovator-under-35/|title=AMPLIFIES Ghana Partner Isaac Sesi Wins MIT Innovator Under 35 \u2013 WISHH|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soygrowers.com/news-releases/amplifies-ghana-partner-isaac-sesi-wins-mit-innovator-under-35/|title=AMPLIFIES Ghana Partner Isaac Sesi Wins MIT Innovator Under 35|website=American Soybean Association|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\n== Achievements ==\n\n* GrainMate has won  the GIST Tech-I 2019 and the Empowering People Award.<ref name=\":4\" />\n*\n*Tony Elumelu 2018 Entrepreneurship Programme<ref name=\":3\" />\n*Names MIT Technology review 2019 innovator under 35.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.risingafrica.org/success-stories/technology-and-innovation/science_technology/ghanaian-inventor-isaac-sesi-makes-mit-technology-reviews-list-of-35-innovators-under-35/|title=Ghanaian inventor Isaac Sesi makes MIT Technology Review\u2019s list of 35 Innovators Under 35|last=Africa|first=Rising|date=2019-07-02|website=RisingAfrica.org|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n*Pasco App won Gold in the Freelance\u00a0 Education category of the MTN Apps Challenge Version 4.0 in 2017<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://darteymedia.com/articles/features/entrepreneur-of-the-month-profile-isaac-sesi/|title=Entrepreneur Of The Month Profile: Isaac Sesi|last=Intern|first=Dartey Media|website=Dartey Media|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n*a Next Einstein finalist<ref name=\":3\" />\n*World Summit Awards National winner<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":1\" />\n*GrainMate was placed second in the IDEA category during the Global Entrepreneurship Congress in Bahrain and he was awarded as one of the three winners in the American Society of Mechanical Engineers IShow Kenya Competition.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n*Winner of the GoGettaz Agripreneur Prize receiving $50,000 to pursue career in agri-food.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201909050742.html|title=Africa: Ghana's Isaac Sesi and Botswana's Bonolo Monthe Win the GoGettaz Agripreneur Prize|last=Chironda|first=Melody|date=2019-09-05|website=allAfrica.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n*Africa Prize for Engineering Innovation by the Royal Academy of Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://technovagh.com/2019/12/03/four-ghanaian-startups-shortlisted-for-africa-prize-for-engineering-innovation/|title=Four Ghanaian Startups Shortlisted For Africa Prize For Engineering Innovation|last=Kuuire|first=Joseph-Albert|date=2019-12-03|website=Tech Nova|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref>\n\n== Reference ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian chief executives]]\n[[Category:Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology alumni]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Isaac Sesi.jpg|thumb|Isaac Sesi at the  Africa Prize for Engineering Innovation by the Royal Academy of Engineering.]]\n{{short description|Ghanaian entrepreneur}}'''Isaac Sesi''' is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] [[Entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]], engineer, and the founder of Sesi Technologies, a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] company that solves agricultural and food challenges.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://citinewsroom.com/2019/06/isaac-sesi-named-mit-technology-review-2019-innovator-under-35/|title=Isaac Sesi named MIT Technology Review 2019 Innovator under 35|date=2019-06-26|website=Citinewsroom - Comprehensive News in Ghana, Current Affairs,  Business News , Headlines, Ghana Sports, Entertainment, Politics,|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanacic.org/clients/15577/|title=Sesi Technologies {{!}} GCIC|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> He is known for his development of a moisture meter to help sub-Saharan African farmers reduce [[Post-harvest losses (grains)|post-harvest losses]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.technologyreview.com/lists/innovators-under-35/2019/inventor/isaac-sesi/|title=Isaac Sesi|website=MIT Technology Review|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref><ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.feedthefuture.gov/article/small-gadget-big-impact-young-entrepreneur-fights-food-loss-with-innovation/|title=Small Gadget, Big Impact: Young Entrepreneur Fights Food Loss with Innovation|date=2019-08-30|website=Feed the Future|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\n== Education ==\nSesi is a graduate of the [[Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology|Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST)]] where he studied [[electrical engineering]]. He completed his senior high school education at [[Mfantsipim School]], where he studied general science.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Career and life ==\n\nSesi is known for developing a moisture metre known as GrainMate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vc4a.com/ventures/sesi-technologies-limited/|title=Sesi Technologies Limited|website=VC4A|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> This device allows farmers and grain traders to measure moisture levels of [[maize]], [[wheat]], [[millet]], and other staple.<ref name=\":0\" /> He is also known to have developed FarmSense, a soil sensing solution for smallholder farmers<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.businessworldghana.com/25-year-old-isaac-sesi-ghanas-emerging-agritech-power-house/|title=25-Year-Old Isaac Sesi Is Ghana\u2019s Emerging Agritech Power House|last=webmanager|date=2018-05-26|website=Business World Ghana|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> which made it to the [[Global Innovation through Science and Technology initiative|Global Innovation through Science and Technology]] (GIST) Tech-I Global Pitch competition semifinals.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.feedthefuture.gov/article/small-gadget-big-impact-young-entrepreneur-fights-food-loss-with-innovation/|title=Small Gadget, Big Impact: Young Entrepreneur Fights Food Loss with Innovation|date=2019-08-30|website=Feed the Future|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref> His first company was Invent Electronic Company Limited, started in 2014, Which retails electronic components online.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\nIn 2015, he cofounded Wires & Bytes with other three friends to develop web apps and software-as-a-service applications. In 2016 they developed Pasco, an educational app\u00a0 for university students <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newsghana.com.gh/ghana-to-become-the-largest-app-developers-soon/|title=Ghana To Become The Largest App Developers Soon|last=Ghana|first=News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> \n\nThe following year he co-founded 2eweboys, a creative writing agency.In 2017, Isaac, then a research engineer at the Department of Agricultural and Biosystems Engineering of the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology and Dr Paul Armstrong, a researcher at the United States Department of Agriculture, worked together on a Feed the Future Innovation Lab for the Reduction of Post Harvest Losses Project in partnership with Kansas State University to develop a low-cost moisture meter. The moisture meter was launched at a ceremony in KNUST<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agrilinks.org/post/month-agrilinks-innovations-move-agriculture-forward|title=This Month on Agrilinks: Innovations That Move Agriculture Forward|date=2020-02-03|website=www.agrilinks.org|language=en|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> <ref name=\":4\" />\n\nSince 2018, he has collaborated with different organisations including World Food Programme Ghana, and the\u00a0 Assisting the Management of Poultry and Layer Industries with Feed Improvements and Efficiency Strategies (AMPLIFIES) Ghana Project which is a food for progress program of the [[United States Department of Agriculture|U.S Department of Agriculture]] (USDA) to run post-harvest loss trainings for farmers across Ghana.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wishh.org/amplifies-ghana-partner-isaac-sesi-wins-mit-innovator-under-35/|title=AMPLIFIES Ghana Partner Isaac Sesi Wins MIT Innovator Under 35 \u2013 WISHH|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soygrowers.com/news-releases/amplifies-ghana-partner-isaac-sesi-wins-mit-innovator-under-35/|title=AMPLIFIES Ghana Partner Isaac Sesi Wins MIT Innovator Under 35|website=American Soybean Association|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n\n== Achievements ==\n\n* GrainMate has won  the GIST Tech-I 2019 and the Empowering People Award.<ref name=\":4\" />\n*\n*Tony Elumelu 2018 Entrepreneurship Programme<ref name=\":3\" />\n*Names MIT Technology review 2019 innovator under 35.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.risingafrica.org/success-stories/technology-and-innovation/science_technology/ghanaian-inventor-isaac-sesi-makes-mit-technology-reviews-list-of-35-innovators-under-35/|title=Ghanaian inventor Isaac Sesi makes MIT Technology Review\u2019s list of 35 Innovators Under 35|last=Africa|first=Rising|date=2019-07-02|website=RisingAfrica.org|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n*Pasco App won Gold in the Freelance\u00a0 Education category of the MTN Apps Challenge Version 4.0 in 2017<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://darteymedia.com/articles/features/entrepreneur-of-the-month-profile-isaac-sesi/|title=Entrepreneur Of The Month Profile: Isaac Sesi|last=Intern|first=Dartey Media|website=Dartey Media|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n*a Next Einstein finalist<ref name=\":3\" />\n*World Summit Awards National winner<ref name=\":3\" /><ref name=\":1\" />\n*GrainMate was placed second in the IDEA category during the Global Entrepreneurship Congress in Bahrain and he was awarded as one of the three winners in the American Society of Mechanical Engineers IShow Kenya Competition.<ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":4\" />\n*Winner of the GoGettaz Agripreneur Prize receiving $50,000 to pursue career in agri-food.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201909050742.html|title=Africa: Ghana's Isaac Sesi and Botswana's Bonolo Monthe Win the GoGettaz Agripreneur Prize|last=Chironda|first=Melody|date=2019-09-05|website=allAfrica.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-19}}</ref>\n*Africa Prize for Engineering Innovation by the Royal Academy of Engineering<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://technovagh.com/2019/12/03/four-ghanaian-startups-shortlisted-for-africa-prize-for-engineering-innovation/|title=Four Ghanaian Startups Shortlisted For Africa Prize For Engineering Innovation|last=Kuuire|first=Joseph-Albert|date=2019-12-03|website=Tech Nova|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref>\n\n== Reference ==\n<references />\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian chief executives]]\n[[Category:Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology alumni]]\n